            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Might be misunderstanding, but i think this change is unneeded.\n\nThis basically just makes it so that the `else` branch of this conditional it hit when `diagnostics = {}` was explicitly passed into the context. But in that case, I'd think the caller intentionally wants to say \"there are no diagnostics here\".\n\nYou're changing a `nil` check to a length check (with this PR, the first part of the conditional would be unneeded)",
